definitions.definition: To function improperly due to an error, especially accompanied by error message.
examples: The web-page took a long time to load and errored out.
Remove that line of code and the script should stop erroring there.
This directory errors with a "Permission denied" message.

definitions.definition: To show or contain an error or fault.
examples: The block transmission errored near the start and could not be received.

main_definition: ( computing ) To function improperly due to an error, especially accompanied by error message.
secondary_definitions: ( telecommunications ) To show or contain an error or fault.
